    "id": "2031089382854373554",
    "text": "Axios’s Marc Caputo on Vice President JD Vance or Secretary of State Marco Rubio in 2028: “Donald Trump likes to poll people about, ‘Hey, what do you think about 2028? Who do you the candidate should be?’ And he asks, ‘Marco Rubio or JD Vance?’ He doesn’t want them to run against each other, he wants them to run with each other.” \n\n“But he’s getting a lot of more positive feedback, Trump is, about Rubio at the top of the ticket than Vance. A lot that is just sort of recency bias, and the fact that Marco Rubio has a portfolio: secretary of state, it puts him in the front and center of global affairs, and National Security Advisor, it puts him directly in the White House. The vice president doesn’t quite have that. So as Peter had said, and Aisha had said, he’s sort of going all around and doing all of these interviews, and then he has to live up to what he had said in the past. And it’s just a very difficult balancing act.”",
