    "lang": "en",
    "score": null,
    "quotedTweet": {
      "id": "1941613519314747623",
      "text": "🇺🇸 ELON'S \"AMERICA PARTY\" COULD ACTUALLY SHAKE UP U.S. POLITICS\n\nIf the new America Party, just launched by @elonmusk, gains real traction, it could finally crack the two-party system that has dominated U.S. politics for over 150 years.\n\nAmerica uses a \"first-past-the-post\" electoral system, where only the candidate with the most votes in each district wins. That makes it incredibly hard for third parties to compete, since votes not going to the top two often get wasted.\n\nBut a well-funded, high-profile party like Elon’s could disrupt that. It could pull support from both Republicans and Democrats, swing close races, and force the major parties to change their platforms to stay competitive.\n\nIf it reaches critical mass, it might even push for reforms, like ranked-choice voting, that make space for more voices.\n\nThis isn’t just about branding. It’s about rewriting the rules of the game.",
      "author": {
        "screenName": "MarioNawfal",
        "name": "Mario Nawfal"
      }
    }
  },
